FBIS4-57972 "drlat103_j_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-103 Daily Report 27 May 1994 Panama ARI Board Accepts Resignation ARI Board Accepts Resignation PA2705012794 Panama City TVN Television Network in Spanish 0000 GMT 27 May 94 PA2705012794 Panama City TVN Television Network Spanish BFN [From the "TVN News" newscast] [Text] This afternoon, the Interoceanic Region Authority [ARI] Board of Directors issued a communique accepting the resignation of General Manager Juan Jose Blau. According to the communique, which consists of three paragraphs, the majority of the Board members decided to accept the resignation, which will become effective on 30 June, a date mentioned in the letter that Blau addressed to the organization. The directors' decision was reached after a meeting held on Wednesday, 25 May. The communique underlines the fact that General Manager Blau has participated in very important ARI activities. The document further states that Blau leaves a trail of honesty and devotion to duty, which merits recognition. The document is signed by ARI President Dr. Carlos A. Mendoza.
